OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FGovernment backs bill to   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fpromote use of British Sign
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5FLanguage                   
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A bill which would make British Sign   
OL,6, Language a legally recognised language 
OL,7, has received government backing.       
OL,9,FThe proposed law, which passed its     
OL,10,Ffirst hurdle in the Commons on Friday, 
OL,11,Fwould require public bodies to promote 
OL,12,Fthe language.                          
OL,14,FActor Rose Ayling-Ellis has been one of
OL,15,Fthose campaigning for the change.      
OL,17,FThe bill was put forward by Labour's   
OL,18,FRosie Cooper who said it would send "a 
OL,19,Fclear message that they (the deaf      
OL,20,Fcommunity) deserve equal access".      
